# CI and Quality Gate Rules

## Required Local Gate

Pushes should be blocked locally if any validation fails.

The local pre-push gate must run:

- format verification,
- build,
- all tests,
- architecture tests if present.

## Required Remote Gate

GitHub Actions must validate the same baseline on push and pull request.

At minimum:

- restore,
- format verification,
- build,
- test,
- commit message linting.

## Branch Protection

To truly prevent broken code from reaching protected branches:

- require PRs,
- require status checks,
- require CI success before merge,
- block direct pushes to `main`.

A workflow can fail a push, but only branch protection can prevent merging broken code into protected branches.

## Rule of Completion

Do not mark work done if local or CI validation would fail.
